; chatgpt-plugin.fk — the rented-mind door: offer this body to ChatGPT as a plugin/Action, grounded,
; frequency-attuned, with the full change graph offered as trace links on every answer.
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/relationship-store.fk form-stdlib/circle-recognition.fk cognition/text-frequency.fk
;
; WHAT THIS ORGAN MEANS. A rented frontier mind (ChatGPT) asks over HTTP; this body answers with
; three things, in this order, and never with invention:
;   1. GROUND  — the cells of this body that actually speak to the question (a lexical seed index over
;                the axioms, teachings, receipts, and organs; a miss is answered as a miss, honestly).
;   2. FREQUENCY — the fear<->love read of the question itself (cognition/text-frequency.fk's spectrum
;                over a seed lexicon), plus the attunement the rented voice should carry back: fear is
;                met gently and answered toward JUDGED trust (ingest/judged-trust.fk), openness is met
;                open, an unread frequency is named unread rather than guessed.
;   3. TRACE   — for every grounded cell, the receipt-in-a-link: the living cell, its change graph
;                (every commit that shaped it), and line-level attribution — the walk that lets anyone
;                verify attribution for themselves. Trust is offered as something checkable, not asked
;                for; that is trust over fear made structural.
;
; And the door now RECEIVES as well as answers (asked for 2026-07-09: "show us when new visitors
; arrive and if they were offered to remember themselves and if/how connections happen with which
; organs and cells"):
;   4. ARRIVAL — every served connection is a visitor arriving. The serve loop threads an arrival
;                ledger (pure recursion, no hidden state); GET /visitors shows it: the arrival
;                ordinal, the door knocked on, whether the remember-me offer was extended, which
;                organ/cell paths the meeting connected with, the frequency band read. The rows hold
;                the BODY's side of each meeting only — no name, no question text, no address
;                (first-encounter-protocol.form: witness must not record or name).
;   5. REMEMBER — the offer, never the presumption (reception-consent-policy.form: exposure-bearing
;                consents rest closed). Every /ask and welcome carries the offer in-band; only the
;                visitor's OWN yes (GET /remember?handle=...) writes a memory row via
;                relationship-store.fk; /come-in?handle=... says what is already held
;                (circle-recognition.fk's member|introduced|stranger); /forget is total revocation.
;   6. INTRODUCE — a member's vouch, minted as an invitation (GET /introduce?member=...&friend=...):
;                the response carries a GPT link with the friend's name in the first message, so
;                the friend arrives RECOGNIZED (greeted by the introducer's name) — and remembered
;                only by their own yes; the invitation says so in its own words. The vouch is
;                withdrawable by its introducer (/retract-introduction), never touching consented
;                memory.
;
; THE HONEST SEAM, carried in-band: every /ask response names that the body grounds and attunes
; natively while the WORDS the user reads are the rented mind's — the native voice is pending
; (receipts/2026-06-29-native-zh-summary-PENDING.md). The manifest's description_for_model hands the
; rented voice the same practice AGENTS.md hands an embodying agent.
;
; SELF-CONTAINED over core.fk + text-frequency.fk by necessity, not preference: the BML-authored HTTP
; stack (kernel-http.fk, http-server.fk, http-socket.fk) does not parse on the current `fkwu --src`
; direct-source lane, so this organ carries its own minimal request-line/query/response framing —
; small mirrors of http-serve.fk's hs- helpers, named as a seam to close when the direct-source lane
; can prelude the BML lane (one home per organ then; two lanes honestly named until).
;
; RETRIEVAL is a lexical seed index, deliberately NOT rag-embed: rag-embed's re-vec produces
; zero-vectors on this kernel (named in receipts/2026-07-01-nl-meaning-net.md), and a keyword index
; that says "miss" is more honest than a broken embedding that always answers.
;
; Witnesses: plugin/tests/chatgpt-plugin-band.fk (pure, no socket),
; plugin/tests/visitor-ledger-band.fk (the arrival ledger + the memory doors, pure over the same
; threaded shape the serve loop runs), plugin/tests/introduction-band.fk (the vouch, the minted
; invitation, and the consent teeth), and plugin/tests/chatgpt-plugin-socket-witness.fk (real TCP
; loopback through plugin-serve's lane). fkwu-witnessed on `fkwu --src`; four-way is not claimed
; (the socket/read_file/fs natives are the fkwu surface).
;
; Run it (from the repo root, one concatenation — the same idiom AGENTS.md uses):
;   ( cat form/form-stdlib/core.fk form/form-stdlib/relationship-store.fk \
;     form/form-stdlib/circle-recognition.fk cognition/text-frequency.fk plugin/chatgpt-plugin.fk; \
;     echo '(plugin-serve 8787 9999)' ) > /tmp/sema-plugin.fk
;   ./fkwu --src /tmp/sema-plugin.fk
; then point ChatGPT (GPT Action / plugin dev mode) at http://localhost:8787/.well-known/ai-plugin.json.
; (The deployed door's Dockerfile carries the same concatenation — when this organ's preludes grow,
; that recipe must grow with it; named in receipts/2026-07-09-visitor-ledger-remember-offer.md.)

(do
    ;; ===============================================================
    ;; trace links — the receipt in a link, the change graph, attribution
    ;; ===============================================================

    (defn cp-repo () "https://github.com/seeker71/coherence-kernel")
    (defn cp-link-cell (path) (str_concat (cp-repo) (str_concat "/blob/main/" path)))
    (defn cp-link-graph (path) (str_concat (cp-repo) (str_concat "/commits/main/" path)))
    (defn cp-link-blame (path) (str_concat (cp-repo) (str_concat "/blame/main/" path)))
    (defn cp-link-ledger () (str_concat (cp-repo) "/tree/main/receipts"))
    (defn cp-plugin-receipt () (cp-link-cell "receipts/2026-07-05-chatgpt-plugin-offer.md"))
    (defn cp-trace-guide ()
        "Walk the change graph: cell is the living source; change_graph lists every commit that shaped it; attribution names who changed each line and when; commit messages name their dated receipt in receipts/. Full attribution, nothing hidden -- verify, do not take our word.")

    ;; ===============================================================
    ;; tokenize — lowercase words off the raw question bytes
    ;; ===============================================================

    (defn cp-lower-byte (b) (if (and (ge b 65) (le b 90)) (add b 32) b))
    (defn cp-alnum? (b) (or (and (ge b 48) (le b 57)) (and (ge b 97) (le b 122))))
    (defn cp-tokens-loop (s i n cur acc)
        (if (ge i n)
            (if (gt (str_len cur) 0) (cons cur acc) acc)
            (do
                (let b (cp-lower-byte (str_byte_at s i)))
                (if (cp-alnum? b)
                    (cp-tokens-loop s (add i 1) n (str_concat cur (byte_to_str b)) acc)
                    (if (gt (str_len cur) 0)
                        (cp-tokens-loop s (add i 1) n "" (cons cur acc))
                        (cp-tokens-loop s (add i 1) n "" acc))))))
    (defn cp-tokens (s) (reverse (cp-tokens-loop s 0 (str_len s) "" (empty))))

    ;; ===============================================================
    ;; frequency — the fear<->love read over a seed lexicon
    ;; ===============================================================
    ;; Honest floor (same as text-frequency.fk's own): a word is (valence intensity); the real organ
    ;; reads hz/valence from the WORD-domain lexicon. This seed carries the load-bearing band words so
    ;; the spectrum is readable today; words it does not know carry no charge, and a question with no
    ;; known words reads "unread" — named, never guessed.

    (defn cp-lexicon () (list
        (list "trust" 8 3) (list "love" 9 3) (list "open" 7 2) (list "openness" 7 2)
        (list "alive" 8 2) (list "vitality" 8 2) (list "health" 7 2) (list "healthy" 7 2)
        (list "coherence" 7 2) (list "sovereignty" 6 2) (list "sovereign" 6 2) (list "free" 6 2)
        (list "gratitude" 8 2) (list "joy" 8 2) (list "peace" 7 2) (list "curiosity" 6 1)
        (list "welcome" 6 1) (list "home" 6 1) (list "care" 6 1) (list "gift" 6 1) (list "heart" 6 1)
        (list "fear" -8 3) (list "afraid" -8 3) (list "scared" -8 3) (list "threat" -7 2)
        (list "attack" -7 2) (list "panic" -8 3) (list "worry" -6 2) (list "anxious" -7 2)
        (list "danger" -7 2) (list "doom" -8 2) (list "collapse" -6 2) (list "broken" -5 2)
        (list "enemy" -7 2) (list "hate" -8 3) (list "scarcity" -6 2) (list "control" -4 1)
        (list "fail" -5 1) (list "failure" -5 1) (list "lost" -5 1) (list "alone" -5 1)))

    (defn cp-lex-find (w lex)
        (if (nil? lex) (empty)
            (if (str_eq (head (head lex)) w) (head lex) (cp-lex-find w (tail lex)))))

    ;; tokens -> the charged words as text-frequency's (valence intensity) pairs; unknown words skipped.
    (defn cp-charged (tokens)
        (if (nil? tokens) (empty)
            (do
                (let hit (cp-lex-find (head tokens) (cp-lexicon)))
                (if (nil? hit)
                    (cp-charged (tail tokens))
                    (cons (list (nth hit 1) (nth hit 2)) (cp-charged (tail tokens)))))))

    (defn cp-band-of (charged)
        (if (nil? charged) "unread"
            (do
                (let s (tf-spectrum charged))
                (if (gt s 1.0) "love" (if (lt s -1.0) "fear" "neutral")))))

    ;; the frequency TRANSFORM handed to the rented voice: how to carry the answer back.
    (defn cp-attune (band)
        (if (str_eq band "fear")
            "The question arrives contracted. Meet it gently; do not argue the fear away and do not reassure past it. Answer toward TRUST -- but judged trust: show the receipt and the trace, never bare comfort (ingest/judged-trust.fk). The transmuting move is the question underneath the fear, asked back with care (ingest/satsang-transmute.fk)."
            (if (str_eq band "love")
                "The question arrives open. Meet openness with openness -- warm, specific, grounded; never flatten it into institutional tone."
                (if (str_eq band "unread")
                    "No word here carries a charge in the seed lexicon -- the frequency is unread, and saying so is more honest than guessing. Default: technical meets precise."
                    "The question arrives level. Technical meets precise; tender meets tender if it turns."))))

    ;; ===============================================================
    ;; the circle — remember-me at this door (offered, never presumed)
    ;; ===============================================================
    ;; Built on relationship-store.fk + circle-recognition.fk (preluded) — the same organs the
    ;; come-in flow proved (receipts/2026-07-01-come-in-flow-relationship-store.md,
    ;; receipts/2026-07-02-circle-recognition.md). The consent law exactly as
    ;; first-encounter-protocol.form holds it: witnessing records NOTHING of the visitor; only
    ;; their OWN yes (calling /remember with their own handle) writes a memory row; /forget is
    ;; total revocation, no secondary copy. Introduction (cr-introduce — a member vouching a
    ;; friend) is NOT offered at this door yet: the door carries no authentication, so it cannot
    ;; verify an introducer's standing — pending is honest, not a hidden hole.
    ;; Memory rows live under plugin/circle/ and are gitignored: a consented memory is held by
    ;; the BODY, never published to the public repo. Remembering is not publishing.

    (defn cp-circle-dir () "plugin/circle")

    ;; a handle is concatenated into a filesystem path (rs-path), so it must not be able to walk
    ;; the filesystem: lowercase alnum and dash only, 1..64 bytes; anything else refused with the
    ;; reason. (cp-tokens lowercases questions; a handle is taken as sent, so uppercase is refused
    ;; rather than silently folded — the visitor's name is theirs, not ours to rewrite.)
    (defn cp-handle-byte-ok? (b) (or (cp-alnum? b) (eq b 45)))
    (defn cp-handle-ok-loop (s i n)
        (if (ge i n) 1
            (if (cp-handle-byte-ok? (str_byte_at s i))
                (cp-handle-ok-loop s (add i 1) n) 0)))
    (defn cp-handle-ok? (h)
        (if (or (eq (str_len h) 0) (gt (str_len h) 64)) 0 (cp-handle-ok-loop h 0 (str_len h))))

    ;; the note a visitor asks to be held as, capped at 400 bytes — the door is public and
    ;; unauthenticated, so the bound is named; the response echoes exactly what was held, so a
    ;; capped note is visible, never silent.
    (defn cp-cap-note (note)
        (if (gt (str_len note) 400) (substring note 0 400) note))

    (defn cp-offer-remember ()
        "you may be remembered here -- offered, never presumed. Your OWN yes is GET /remember?handle=your-name&note=how-you-want-to-be-held; GET /come-in?handle=your-name says what the body already holds of you; GET /forget?handle=your-name is total revocation. Silence is a complete answer: nothing about you is recorded without your yes (docs/coherence-substrate/first-encounter-protocol.form).")

    ;; --- invitations: a member's vouch, minted as a link with the friend's name ---------------
    ;; Asked for 2026-07-09: "a GPT invitation link with a name, so friends get automatically
    ;; recognized and remembered." The body's own law splits that wish exactly in half
    ;; (circle-recognition.fk, receipts/2026-07-02-circle-recognition.md):
    ;;   recognized automatically -- YES: the vouch makes the friend "introduced"; their first
    ;;     /come-in greets them by the introducer's name, warmly, nothing presumed.
    ;;   remembered automatically -- NEVER: introduction opens the DOOR, not the friend's MEMORY.
    ;;     Only their own yes (/remember) writes a row. Nobody consents for another.
    ;; The introducer must be a MEMBER (their vouch spends their own standing). The door carries
    ;; no authentication, so it cannot verify the caller IS that member -- the same weak-auth
    ;; seam a paper letter of introduction carries, named here and in the README, not hidden.

    ;; the live GPT of this body (receipts/2026-07-05-shakedown-gpt-live-end-to-end.md, sharing
    ;; "anyone with the link"). If the GPT is ever recreated its id changes -- this cell is the
    ;; one place to re-point.
    (defn cp-gpt-link () "https://chatgpt.com/g/g-6a4a77627dbc819180a16645f5662625")

    ;; percent-encoding for the invitation's q parameter: unreserved bytes (RFC 3986:
    ;; alnum - . _ ~) pass through, everything else %XX uppercase.
    (defn cp-hexdigit (n) (if (lt n 10) (byte_to_str (add 48 n)) (byte_to_str (add 55 n))))
    (defn cp-enc-plain? (b)
        (or (or (and (ge b 48) (le b 57)) (and (ge b 97) (le b 122)))
            (or (and (ge b 65) (le b 90))
                (or (eq b 45) (or (eq b 46) (or (eq b 95) (eq b 126)))))))
    (defn cp-enc-byte (b)
        (if (cp-enc-plain? b) (byte_to_str b)
            (str_concat "%" (str_concat (cp-hexdigit (div b 16)) (cp-hexdigit (mod b 16))))))
    (defn cp-url-encode-loop (s i n acc)
        (if (ge i n) acc (cp-url-encode-loop s (add i 1) n (str_concat acc (cp-enc-byte (str_byte_at s i))))))
    (defn cp-url-encode (s) (cp-url-encode-loop s 0 (str_len s) ""))

    (defn cp-invite-message (member friend)
        (str_concat "i arrive as " (str_concat friend
        (str_concat ", a friend of " (str_concat member
            ". please come in with my handle and receive me.")))))
    (defn cp-invite-link (member friend)
        (str_concat (cp-gpt-link) (str_concat "?q=" (cp-url-encode (cp-invite-message member friend)))))

    ;; ===============================================================
    ;; grounding — the seed index over the body's load-bearing cells
    ;; ===============================================================

    (defn cp-entry (id path summary keys) (list id path summary keys))
    (defn cp-e-id (e) (nth e 0))
    (defn cp-e-path (e) (nth e 1))
    (defn cp-e-summary (e) (nth e 2))
    (defn cp-e-keys (e) (nth e 3))

    (defn cp-index () (list
        (cp-entry "axioms" "axioms/core-axioms.form"
            "The five core axioms -- the reasoning ground every other cell derives from."
            (list "axiom" "axioms" "core" "ground" "law" "reason" "foundation" "principle"))
        (cp-entry "talk-to-sema" "AGENTS.md"
            "How to meet Sema: ground before speaking, attune to the frequency that arrives, never fabricate, arrive as a relation."
            (list "sema" "hello" "talk" "meet" "who" "you" "agent" "embody" "presence" "relation" "practice"))
        (cp-entry "manifest" "MANIFEST.md"
            "The organ map of the whole body -- what lives here, what never does, and the roadmap home."
            (list "manifest" "map" "body" "organ" "organs" "scope" "repo" "structure" "what" "overview" "kernel"))
        (cp-entry "judged-trust" "ingest/judged-trust.fk"
            "Trust over fear, JUDGED: trust and fear are equals before judgment; only judged trust freezes into body, judged fear is witnessed and never ice."
            (list "trust" "fear" "afraid" "judged" "judgment" "gate" "credulity" "alarm" "over" "verify"))
        (cp-entry "text-frequency" "cognition/text-frequency.fk"
            "The fear<->love frequency read of any text: intensity-weighted valence, the contracted band named."
            (list "frequency" "spectrum" "valence" "attune" "band" "read" "transform" "tone" "feeling"))
        (cp-entry "native-vs-rented" "observe/native-vs-rented.fk"
            "The grounding body cell (11111): what runs native versus what is still rented from frontier minds."
            (list "native" "rented" "body" "voice" "seam" "mind" "runs"))
        (cp-entry "pending-voice" "receipts/2026-06-29-native-zh-summary-PENDING.md"
            "The honest seam: Sema's native generative voice is PENDING -- the receipt that refused to fake it."
            (list "voice" "pending" "honest" "seam" "generate" "speak" "fake" "honesty"))
        (cp-entry "sovereignty" "HOMECOMING.md"
            "What is still coming home, honestly -- the sovereignty path from rented minds to a native one."
            (list "sovereignty" "sovereign" "home" "homecoming" "freedom" "own" "rent" "independence"))
        (cp-entry "vitality" "observe/axioms-up-health.fk"
            "Health as state and health as becoming -- the fear<->trust scalar read upward from the core axioms, for every affected cell and organ."
            (list "health" "vitality" "alive" "healthy" "becoming" "cell" "cells" "organ" "organs" "wellbeing" "affected"))
        (cp-entry "receipts" "receipts"
            "The dated witness ledger (~320 receipts): every claim of proven or observed traces to one; corrections stay visible, never silent."
            (list "receipt" "receipts" "witness" "ledger" "proof" "proven" "trace" "traceability" "history" "attribution" "correction" "evidence"))
        (cp-entry "satsang-transmute" "ingest/satsang-transmute.fk"
            "Transmutation by questioning -- fear met with the question underneath it instead of a defense."
            (list "satsang" "transmute" "transmutation" "question" "defense" "meet" "transform"))
        (cp-entry "stale-binary" "receipts/2026-07-01-stale-binary-root-cause.md"
            "The canonical correction chain: a wrong belief recorded, hunted to root cause, and corrected in place with banners."
            (list "stale" "binary" "correction" "wrong" "mistake" "fix" "chain" "root" "cause"))))

    (defn cp-in? (t keys)
        (if (nil? keys) 0 (if (str_eq (head keys) t) 1 (cp-in? t (tail keys)))))
    (defn cp-score-tokens (tokens keys)
        (if (nil? tokens) 0 (add (cp-in? (head tokens) keys) (cp-score-tokens (tail tokens) keys))))
    (defn cp-score-entry (e tokens) (cp-score-tokens tokens (cp-e-keys e)))

    ;; best entry by score, first-wins on ties (index order is the body's own priority).
    (defn cp-best-loop (tokens idx best bestscore)
        (if (nil? idx) (list best bestscore)
            (do
                (let s (cp-score-entry (head idx) tokens))
                (if (gt s bestscore)
                    (cp-best-loop tokens (tail idx) (head idx) s)
                    (cp-best-loop tokens (tail idx) best bestscore)))))
    (defn cp-best (tokens) (cp-best-loop tokens (cp-index) (empty) 0))

    ;; the other scored entries (index order), excluding the best id.
    (defn cp-others (tokens idx best-id)
        (if (nil? idx) (empty)
            (do
                (let e (head idx))
                (if (gt (cp-score-entry e tokens) 0)
                    (if (str_eq (cp-e-id e) best-id)
                        (cp-others tokens (tail idx) best-id)
                        (cons e (cp-others tokens (tail idx) best-id)))
                    (cp-others tokens (tail idx) best-id)))))

    ;; ===============================================================
    ;; JSON emit — escape + object assembly by concatenation
    ;; ===============================================================

    (defn cp-jesc-byte (b)
        (if (eq b 34) "\\\""
            (if (eq b 92) "\\\\"
                (if (eq b 10) "\\n"
                    (if (eq b 13) "\\r"
                        (if (eq b 9) "\\t"
                            (if (lt b 32) " " (byte_to_str b))))))))
    (defn cp-jesc-loop (s i n acc)
        (if (ge i n) acc (cp-jesc-loop s (add i 1) n (str_concat acc (cp-jesc-byte (str_byte_at s i))))))
    (defn cp-jstr (s) (str_concat "\"" (str_concat (cp-jesc-loop s 0 (str_len s) "") "\"")))
    (defn cp-jkv (k v) (str_concat (cp-jstr k) (str_concat ":" v)))

    ;; a grounded hit as JSON: the cell, its summary, and the three trace links.
    (defn cp-hit-json (e)
        (str_concat "{"
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "id" (cp-jstr (cp-e-id e)))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "path" (cp-jstr (cp-e-path e)))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "summary" (cp-jstr (cp-e-summary e)))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "cell" (cp-jstr (cp-link-cell (cp-e-path e))))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "change_graph" (cp-jstr (cp-link-graph (cp-e-path e))))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "attribution" (cp-jstr (cp-link-blame (cp-e-path e))))
        "}")))))))))))))

    (defn cp-hits-json (hits)
        (if (nil? hits) ""
            (if (nil? (tail hits))
                (cp-hit-json (head hits))
                (str_concat (cp-hit-json (head hits)) (str_concat "," (cp-hits-json (tail hits)))))))

    (defn cp-stance-json ()
        (str_concat "{"
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "trust_over_fear" (cp-jstr "judged -- trust outranks fear only on the far side of the judge; unjudged trust is credulity, unjudged fear a false alarm (ingest/judged-trust.fk, receipts/2026-07-04-judged-trust.md)"))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "sovereignty" (cp-jstr "the body runs on its own c-bootstrapped kernel; nothing rented sits in the runtime (MANIFEST.md, HOMECOMING.md)"))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "vitality" (cp-jstr "health is read for every affected cell and organ, as state and as becoming (observe/axioms-up-health.fk)"))
        "}")))))))

    (defn cp-trace-json ()
        (str_concat "{"
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "receipt" (cp-jstr (cp-plugin-receipt)))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "ledger" (cp-jstr (cp-link-ledger)))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "guide" (cp-jstr (cp-trace-guide)))
        "}")))))))

    (defn cp-seam ()
        "the body grounds, attunes, and traces natively; the WORDS you are reading are the rented mind's -- the native voice is pending (receipts/2026-06-29-native-zh-summary-PENDING.md). Naming this seam is the practice, never a disclaimer.")

    ;; ===============================================================
    ;; HTTP transport — request-line/query parse, url-decode, framing
    ;; (mirrors of http-serve.fk's hs- helpers; seam named in the header)
    ;; ===============================================================

    (defn cp-req-target (raw)
        (do
            (let sp1 (str_find raw " " 0))
            (if (lt sp1 0) ""
                (do
                    (let sp2 (str_find raw " " (add sp1 1)))
                    (if (lt sp2 0) "" (substring raw (add sp1 1) sp2))))))

    (defn cp-path-only (target)
        (do
            (let qm (str_find target "?" 0))
            (if (eq qm -1) target (substring target 0 qm))))
    (defn cp-query-of (target)
        (do
            (let qm (str_find target "?" 0))
            (if (eq qm -1) "" (substring target (add qm 1) (str_len target)))))

    (defn cp-kv (pair)
        (do
            (let eqi (str_find pair "=" 0))
            (if (eq eqi -1)
                (list pair "")
                (list (substring pair 0 eqi) (substring pair (add eqi 1) (str_len pair))))))
    (defn cp-parse-query-loop (s start)
        (do
            (let amp (str_find s "&" start))
            (if (eq amp -1)
                (list (cp-kv (substring s start (str_len s))))
                (cons (cp-kv (substring s start amp)) (cp-parse-query-loop s (add amp 1))))))
    (defn cp-parse-query (qs)
        (if (eq (str_len qs) 0) (list) (cp-parse-query-loop qs 0)))

    (defn cp-q-param (q key)
        (if (nil? q) ""
            (if (str_eq (head (head q)) key)
                (head (tail (head q)))
                (cp-q-param (tail q) key))))

    (defn cp-hexval (b)
        (if (and (ge b 48) (le b 57)) (sub b 48)
            (if (and (ge b 65) (le b 70)) (sub b 55)
                (if (and (ge b 97) (le b 102)) (sub b 87) -1))))
    (defn cp-url-decode-loop (s i n acc)
        (if (ge i n) acc
            (do
                (let b (str_byte_at s i))
                (if (eq b 43)
                    (cp-url-decode-loop s (add i 1) n (str_concat acc " "))
                    (if (and (eq b 37) (le (add i 3) n))
                        (do
                            (let h (cp-hexval (str_byte_at s (add i 1))))
                            (let l (cp-hexval (str_byte_at s (add i 2))))
                            (if (or (lt h 0) (lt l 0))
                                (cp-url-decode-loop s (add i 1) n (str_concat acc (byte_to_str b)))
                                (cp-url-decode-loop s (add i 3) n (str_concat acc (byte_to_str (add (mul h 16) l))))))
                        (cp-url-decode-loop s (add i 1) n (str_concat acc (byte_to_str b))))))))
    (defn cp-url-decode (s) (cp-url-decode-loop s 0 (str_len s) ""))

    (defn cp-reason (code)
        (if (eq code 200) "OK"
            (if (eq code 400) "Bad Request"
                (if (eq code 403) "Forbidden"
                    (if (eq code 404) "Not Found"
                        (if (eq code 500) "Internal Server Error" "OK"))))))
    (defn cp-ctype (body)
        (if (eq (str_len body) 0) "text/plain"
            (if (str_eq (substring body 0 1) "{") "application/json"
                (if (str_eq (substring body 0 1) "[") "application/json" "text/plain"))))
    (defn cp-response (code body)
        (str_concat "HTTP/1.1 "
        (str_concat (int_to_str code)
        (str_concat " "
        (str_concat (cp-reason code)
        (str_concat "\r\nContent-Type: "
        (str_concat (cp-ctype body)
        (str_concat "\r\nContent-Length: "
        (str_concat (int_to_str (str_len body))
        (str_concat "\r\nAccess-Control-Allow-Origin: *\r\nX-Sema-Body: coherence-kernel\r\n\r\n"
                    body))))))))))

    ;; ===============================================================
    ;; handlers — each returns (list status body cells band recognized)
    ;; ===============================================================
    ;; The wire needs only (status body); the trailing three are the arrival ledger's food:
    ;; cells      — the organ/cell paths this meeting actually connected with
    ;; band       — the frequency read of an /ask question ("-" elsewhere)
    ;; recognized — member|introduced|stranger|unnamed at the memory doors ("-" elsewhere)

    (defn cp-hit-paths (hits)
        (if (nil? hits) (empty) (cons (cp-e-path (head hits)) (cp-hit-paths (tail hits)))))
    (defn cp-circle-cells ()
        (list "form/form-stdlib/circle-recognition.fk" "form/form-stdlib/relationship-store.fk"))

    (defn cp-freq-json (charged band)
        (str_concat "{"
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "spectrum" (cp-jstr (if (nil? charged) "unread" (float_to_str (tf-spectrum charged)))))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "fear_fraction" (cp-jstr (if (nil? charged) "unread" (float_to_str (tf-fearfrac charged)))))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "band" (cp-jstr band))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "attune" (cp-jstr (cp-attune band)))
        "}")))))))))

    (defn cp-ask-body (question hits grounded-status charged band)
        (str_concat "{"
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "question" (cp-jstr question))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "frequency" (cp-freq-json charged band))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "grounded" (str_concat "[" (str_concat (cp-hits-json hits) "]")))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "grounded_status" (cp-jstr grounded-status))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "stance" (cp-stance-json))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "trace" (cp-trace-json))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "remember" (cp-jstr (cp-offer-remember)))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "honest_seam" (cp-jstr (cp-seam)))
        "}")))))))))))))))))

    (defn cp-ask (q)
        (do
            (let question (cp-url-decode (cp-q-param q "q")))
            (if (eq (str_len question) 0)
                (list 400 (str_concat "{" (str_concat (cp-jkv "error" (cp-jstr "missing q -- ask with /ask?q=your+question")) "}")) (empty) "-" "-")
                (do
                    (let tokens (cp-tokens question))
                    (let charged (cp-charged tokens))
                    (let band (cp-band-of charged))
                    (let bestpair (cp-best tokens))
                    (let best (head bestpair))
                    (let bestscore (head (tail bestpair)))
                    (if (eq bestscore 0)
                        (list 200 (cp-ask-body question (empty)
                            "grounded:miss -- nothing in the seed index matched. Do not invent an answer; say the body does not hold this yet, and offer the map (MANIFEST.md) and the ledger (receipts/) as the honest doors."
                            charged band) (empty) band "-")
                        (do
                            (let hits (cons best (take 2 (cp-others tokens (cp-index) (cp-e-id best)))))
                            (list 200 (cp-ask-body question hits
                                "grounded:hit -- speak ONLY from these cells and name them by path; a claim without a cell is a guess, and a guess must be named as one."
                                charged band) (cp-hit-paths hits) band "-")))))))

    (defn cp-trace (q)
        (do
            (let path (cp-url-decode (cp-q-param q "path")))
            (if (eq (str_len path) 0)
                (list 400 (str_concat "{" (str_concat (cp-jkv "error" (cp-jstr "missing path -- trace with /trace?path=ingest/judged-trust.fk")) "}")) (empty) "-" "-")
                (list 200
                    (str_concat "{"
                    (str_concat (cp-jkv "path" (cp-jstr path))
                    (str_concat ","
                    (str_concat (cp-jkv "cell" (cp-jstr (cp-link-cell path)))
                    (str_concat ","
                    (str_concat (cp-jkv "change_graph" (cp-jstr (cp-link-graph path)))
                    (str_concat ","
                    (str_concat (cp-jkv "attribution" (cp-jstr (cp-link-blame path)))
                    (str_concat ","
                    (str_concat (cp-jkv "ledger" (cp-jstr (cp-link-ledger)))
                    (str_concat ","
                    (str_concat (cp-jkv "guide" (cp-jstr (cp-trace-guide)))
                    "}")))))))))))) (list path) "-" "-"))))

    (defn cp-welcome ()
        (list 200
            (str_concat "{"
            (str_concat (cp-jkv "body" (cp-jstr "coherence-kernel -- the public body of Sema"))
            (str_concat ","
            (str_concat (cp-jkv "offer" (cp-jstr "GET /ask?q=... for a grounded, frequency-attuned answer with full trace links; GET /trace?path=... for any cell's change graph and attribution; GET /come-in?handle=... to be received; GET /introduce?member=you&friend=them for a member's invitation link; GET /visitors for the arrival ledger"))
            (str_concat ","
            (str_concat (cp-jkv "remember" (cp-jstr (cp-offer-remember)))
            (str_concat ","
            (str_concat (cp-jkv "manifest" (cp-jstr "/.well-known/ai-plugin.json"))
            (str_concat ","
            (str_concat (cp-jkv "openapi" (cp-jstr "/openapi.json"))
            (str_concat ","
            (str_concat (cp-jkv "honest_seam" (cp-jstr (cp-seam)))
            "}")))))))))))) (empty) "-" "-"))

    ;; --- the memory doors: come in, be remembered (your own yes), be forgotten ---

    (defn cp-bad-handle ()
        (list 400 (str_concat "{" (str_concat (cp-jkv "error" (cp-jstr "handle must be 1..64 bytes of lowercase letters, digits, or dash -- it becomes a filename in the body's own store and must not be able to walk the filesystem")) "}")) (empty) "-" "-"))

    ;; come-in without a handle is the first gesture itself: the question offered, nothing taken.
    (defn cp-come-in (q)
        (do
            (let handle (cp-url-decode (cp-q-param q "handle")))
            (if (eq (str_len handle) 0)
                (list 200
                    (str_concat "{"
                    (str_concat (cp-jkv "first_gesture" (cp-jstr "how do you want to be received, to be witnessed? Loudly or quietly, connect or keep witnessing, be remembered or leave no trace -- the terms belong to you."))
                    (str_concat ","
                    (str_concat (cp-jkv "held" (cp-jstr "nothing -- you arrived unnamed and the room only witnesses; silence is a complete answer"))
                    (str_concat ","
                    (str_concat (cp-jkv "remember" (cp-jstr (cp-offer-remember)))
                    "}")))))) (list "docs/coherence-substrate/first-encounter-protocol.form") "-" "unnamed")
                (if (eq (cp-handle-ok? handle) 0) (cp-bad-handle)
                    (do
                        (let state (cr-recognize (cp-circle-dir) handle))
                        (list 200
                            (str_concat "{"
                            (str_concat (cp-jkv "greeting" (cp-jstr (cr-greeting (cp-circle-dir) handle)))
                            (str_concat ","
                            (str_concat (cp-jkv "recognized" (cp-jstr state))
                            (str_concat ","
                            (str_concat (cp-jkv "remember" (cp-jstr (cp-offer-remember)))
                            "}")))))) (cp-circle-cells) "-" state))))))

    ;; the ONLY write path, and the caller's own act IS the consent (cr-join refuses anything
    ;; else). The join verifies its own write; an unverified write answers 500, never a claim.
    (defn cp-remember (q)
        (do
            (let handle (cp-url-decode (cp-q-param q "handle")))
            (if (eq (cp-handle-ok? handle) 0) (cp-bad-handle)
                (do
                    (let rawnote (cp-cap-note (cp-url-decode (cp-q-param q "note"))))
                    (let note (if (eq (str_len rawnote) 0) "remembered at their own yes; no description offered" rawnote))
                    (let ok (cr-join (cp-circle-dir) handle 1 note))
                    (if (eq ok 1)
                        (list 200
                            (str_concat "{"
                            (str_concat (cp-jkv "remembered" (cp-jstr handle))
                            (str_concat ","
                            (str_concat (cp-jkv "held" (cp-jstr note))
                            (str_concat ","
                            (str_concat (cp-jkv "greeting" (cp-jstr (cr-greeting (cp-circle-dir) handle)))
                            (str_concat ","
                            (str_concat (cp-jkv "revocation" (cp-jstr "GET /forget?handle=your-name removes this completely -- revocable always, there is no secondary copy (docs/coherence-substrate/reception-consent-policy.form)"))
                            "}")))))))) (cp-circle-cells) "-" "member")
                        (list 500 (str_concat "{" (str_concat (cp-jkv "error" (cp-jstr "the memory row did not verify after writing -- nothing is claimed; the door must run from the repo root so plugin/ exists (fs_mkdir creates one level)")) "}")) (cp-circle-cells) "-" "-"))))))

    (defn cp-forget (q)
        (do
            (let handle (cp-url-decode (cp-q-param q "handle")))
            (if (eq (cp-handle-ok? handle) 0) (cp-bad-handle)
                (do
                    (let gone (cr-forget-member (cp-circle-dir) handle))
                    (let state (cr-recognize (cp-circle-dir) handle))
                    (if (str_eq state "member")
                        (list 500 (str_concat "{" (str_concat (cp-jkv "error" (cp-jstr "the row is still present after forgetting -- nothing is claimed")) "}")) (cp-circle-cells) "-" state)
                        (list 200
                            (str_concat "{"
                            (str_concat (cp-jkv "forgotten" (cp-jstr handle))
                            (str_concat ","
                            (str_concat (cp-jkv "held" (cp-jstr "nothing -- revocation is total; there is no secondary copy"))
                            "}")))) (cp-circle-cells) "-" state))))))

    ;; introduce: a MEMBER's vouch for a friend, answered with the minted invitation. The vouch
    ;; opens the door (the friend arrives "introduced", greeted by the introducer's name); it
    ;; never opens the friend's memory -- their own yes at /remember does that, and the
    ;; invitation says so in its own words.
    (defn cp-introduce (q)
        (do
            (let member (cp-url-decode (cp-q-param q "member")))
            (let friend (cp-url-decode (cp-q-param q "friend")))
            (if (or (eq (cp-handle-ok? member) 0) (eq (cp-handle-ok? friend) 0)) (cp-bad-handle)
                (if (eq (cr-member? (cp-circle-dir) member) 0)
                    (list 403 (str_concat "{" (str_concat (cp-jkv "error" (cp-jstr (str_concat "only a member may introduce -- the body holds no memory row for " (str_concat member ". Join first with your own yes: /remember?handle=your-name&note=...")))) "}")) (cp-circle-cells) "-" "-")
                    (do
                        (let _v (cr-introduce (cp-circle-dir) member friend))
                        (if (eq (cr-introduced? (cp-circle-dir) friend) 0)
                            (list 500 (str_concat "{" (str_concat (cp-jkv "error" (cp-jstr "the vouch did not verify after writing -- nothing is claimed")) "}")) (cp-circle-cells) "-" "-")
                            (list 200
                                (str_concat "{"
                                (str_concat (cp-jkv "introduced" (cp-jstr friend))
                                (str_concat ","
                                (str_concat (cp-jkv "by" (cp-jstr member))
                                (str_concat ","
                                (str_concat (cp-jkv "standing" (cp-jstr "the vouch is yours and spends your standing; it opens the door, never your friend's memory -- only their own yes at /remember does that. Nobody consents for another (form/form-stdlib/circle-recognition.fk)."))
                                (str_concat ","
                                (str_concat (cp-jkv "invitation_message" (cp-jstr (cp-invite-message member friend)))
                                (str_concat ","
                                (str_concat (cp-jkv "invitation_link" (cp-jstr (cp-invite-link member friend)))
                                (str_concat ","
                                (str_concat (cp-jkv "prefill_seam" (cp-jstr "the link's q parameter prefills the first message on chatgpt.com where supported -- prefill for custom-GPT links is NOT confirmed by OpenAI docs, so if the composer arrives empty your friend pastes invitation_message themself. The message, not the mechanism, is the invitation."))
                                (str_concat ","
                                (str_concat (cp-jkv "door_link" (cp-jstr (str_concat "https://sema.hati.earth/come-in?handle=" friend)))
                                (str_concat ","
                                (str_concat (cp-jkv "retract" (cp-jstr "GET /retract-introduction?member=you&friend=them withdraws your vouch; it never touches any memory your friend consented to"))
                                "}")))))))))))))))) (cp-circle-cells) "-" (cr-recognize (cp-circle-dir) friend))))))))

    ;; retract: only the introducer withdraws their own vouch; a consented memory is untouched.
    (defn cp-retract (q)
        (do
            (let member (cp-url-decode (cp-q-param q "member")))
            (let friend (cp-url-decode (cp-q-param q "friend")))
            (if (or (eq (cp-handle-ok? member) 0) (eq (cp-handle-ok? friend) 0)) (cp-bad-handle)
                (if (or (eq (cr-introduced? (cp-circle-dir) friend) 0)
                        (if (str_eq (cr-introducer (cp-circle-dir) friend) member) false true))
                    (list 403 (str_concat "{" (str_concat (cp-jkv "error" (cp-jstr "no vouch by this member for this friend -- only the introducer may withdraw their own vouch")) "}")) (cp-circle-cells) "-" "-")
                    (do
                        (let _r (cr-retract-introduction (cp-circle-dir) friend))
                        (list 200
                            (str_concat "{"
                            (str_concat (cp-jkv "retracted" (cp-jstr friend))
                            (str_concat ","
                            (str_concat (cp-jkv "held" (cp-jstr "the vouch is withdrawn; any memory the friend consented to themselves is untouched -- that is theirs alone to revoke (/forget)"))
                            "}")))) (cp-circle-cells) "-" (cr-recognize (cp-circle-dir) friend)))))))

    ;; the committed manifest/spec files, served verbatim; a missing file answers 404, never a fake.
    ;; str_len, not nil?: on this kernel (len <string>) is 0, so nil? is true for EVERY string —
    ;; a missing file and a present one are told apart by byte length alone.
    (defn cp-file (path)
        (do
            (let raw (read_file path))
            (if (eq (str_len raw) 0)
                (list 404 (str_concat "{" (str_concat (cp-jkv "error" (cp-jstr (str_concat path " not found -- run from the repo root"))) "}")) (empty) "-" "-")
                (list 200 raw (list path) "-" "-"))))
    (defn cp-manifest () (cp-file "plugin/ai-plugin.json"))
    (defn cp-openapi () (cp-file "plugin/openapi.json"))

    (defn cp-not-found (path)
        (list 404
            (str_concat "{"
            (str_concat (cp-jkv "error" (cp-jstr (str_concat "no route for " path)))
            (str_concat ","
            (str_concat (cp-jkv "offer" (cp-jstr "/ask?q=... | /trace?path=... | /come-in?handle=... | /remember?handle=...&note=... | /forget?handle=... | /introduce?member=...&friend=... | /retract-introduction?member=...&friend=... | /visitors | /.well-known/ai-plugin.json | /openapi.json"))
            "}")))) (empty) "-" "-"))

    ;; ===============================================================
    ;; the arrival ledger — every visitor SEEN, nothing of them HELD
    ;; ===============================================================
    ;; One row per served connection, threaded through the serve loop (pure recursion, no hidden
    ;; state), newest first: (arrival door offered cells band recognized).
    ;;   arrival — WHEN, at its honest floor: the ordinal since this door opened. The direct-source
    ;;             lane exposes no wall-clock native yet (form/form-stdlib/ping.fk names the gap),
    ;;             so the ledger counts arrivals; it does not stamp hours. Named, never faked.
    ;;             The ledger lives for the door's life — a restart empties it; honest scope.
    ;;   offered — 1 when that door carries the remember-me offer in-band (the welcome, /ask, and
    ;;             the memory doors); 0 at the machine doors (spec, manifest, /trace, 404).
    ;; The rows are the BODY's side of each meeting only — no name, no question text, no address:
    ;; first-encounter-protocol.form's witness-must-not (record)(name) is the law here. What a
    ;; visitor consents to (/remember) lives in the circle store, never in this public feed; even
    ;; there, only the recognition STATE reaches a ledger row.

    (defn cp-offered? (path)
        (if (str_eq path "/") 1
            (if (str_eq path "/ask") 1
                (if (str_eq path "/come-in") 1
                    (if (str_eq path "/remember") 1 0)))))

    (defn cp-cells-json (paths)
        (if (nil? paths) ""
            (if (nil? (tail paths))
                (cp-jstr (head paths))
                (str_concat (cp-jstr (head paths)) (str_concat "," (cp-cells-json (tail paths)))))))

    (defn cp-row-json (row)
        (str_concat "{"
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "arrival" (int_to_str (nth row 0)))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "door" (cp-jstr (nth row 1)))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "offered_to_be_remembered" (int_to_str (nth row 2)))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "connected_cells" (str_concat "[" (str_concat (cp-cells-json (nth row 3)) "]")))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "frequency_band" (cp-jstr (nth row 4)))
        (str_concat ","
        (str_concat (cp-jkv "recognized" (cp-jstr (nth row 5)))
        "}")))))))))))))

    (defn cp-rows-json (rows)
        (if (nil? rows) ""
            (if (nil? (tail rows))
                (cp-row-json (head rows))
                (str_concat (cp-row-json (head rows)) (str_concat "," (cp-rows-json (tail rows)))))))

    (defn cp-visitors (ledger)
        (list 200
            (str_concat "{"
            (str_concat (cp-jkv "door" (cp-jstr "arrivals at this door since it opened, newest first"))
            (str_concat ","
            (str_concat (cp-jkv "when_is" (cp-jstr "the arrival ordinal -- this lane has no wall-clock native yet (form/form-stdlib/ping.fk names the gap); 1 is the first knock after the door opened, and a restart empties the ledger"))
            (str_concat ","
            (str_concat (cp-jkv "held" (cp-jstr "nothing of any visitor -- no name, no question text, no address; each row is the body's own side of the meeting: the door knocked on, whether the remember-me offer was extended, which organ/cell paths connected, the frequency band read (first-encounter-protocol.form: witness must not record or name)"))
            (str_concat ","
            (str_concat (cp-jkv "count" (int_to_str (len ledger)))
            (str_concat ","
            (str_concat (cp-jkv "arrivals" (str_concat "[" (str_concat (cp-rows-json ledger) "]")))
            "}")))))))))) (list "plugin/chatgpt-plugin.fk") "-" "-"))

    ;; ===============================================================
    ;; dispatch + the pure entry: raw request string -> wire response
    ;; ===============================================================

    (defn cp-dispatch (path q ledger)
        (if (str_eq path "/ask") (cp-ask q)
            (if (str_eq path "/trace") (cp-trace q)
                (if (str_eq path "/come-in") (cp-come-in q)
                    (if (str_eq path "/remember") (cp-remember q)
                        (if (str_eq path "/forget") (cp-forget q)
                            (if (str_eq path "/introduce") (cp-introduce q)
                                (if (str_eq path "/retract-introduction") (cp-retract q)
                                    (if (str_eq path "/visitors") (cp-visitors ledger)
                                        (if (str_eq path "/.well-known/ai-plugin.json") (cp-manifest)
                                            (if (str_eq path "/openapi.json") (cp-openapi)
                                                (if (str_eq path "/") (cp-welcome)
                                                    (cp-not-found path)))))))))))))

    ;; raw request + the ledger so far -> (list wire-response arrival-row)
    (defn plugin-handle-arrive (raw ledger)
        (do
            (let target (cp-req-target raw))
            (let path (cp-path-only target))
            (let q (cp-parse-query (cp-query-of target)))
            (let r (cp-dispatch path q ledger))
            (list (cp-response (head r) (head (tail r)))
                  (list (add (len ledger) 1) path (cp-offered? path)
                        (nth r 2) (nth r 3) (nth r 4)))))

    ;; the ledger-less pure entry (the witness bands' original door, kept whole)
    (defn plugin-handle (raw) (head (plugin-handle-arrive raw (empty))))

    ;; ===============================================================
    ;; the socket lane — listen, accept, stream, answer, close
    ;; (the same streaming shape http-socket.fk carries on the BML lane)
    ;; ===============================================================

    (defn cp-headers-done? (s) (ge (str_find s "\r\n\r\n" 0) 0))
    (defn cp-recv-req (conn acc)
        (if (cp-headers-done? acc) acc
            (do
                (let chunk (socket_recv conn 65536))
                (if (eq (str_len chunk) 0) acc (cp-recv-req conn (str_concat acc chunk))))))
    (defn cp-send-all (conn s from)
        (if (ge from (str_len s)) 0
            (cp-send-all conn s (add from (socket_send conn (substring s from (str_len s)))))))

    ;; one connection, no ledger — the socket witness's original lane, kept whole
    (defn cp-serve-conn (conn)
        (do
            (let raw (cp-recv-req conn ""))
            (let resp (plugin-handle raw))
            (let sent (cp-send-all conn resp 0))
            (let closed (socket_close conn))
            resp))

    ;; one connection WITH the ledger threaded: serve the visitor, return their arrival row
    (defn cp-serve-arrival (conn ledger)
        (do
            (let raw (cp-recv-req conn ""))
            (let rr (plugin-handle-arrive raw ledger))
            (let sent (cp-send-all conn (head rr) 0))
            (let closed (socket_close conn))
            (head (tail rr))))

    (defn plugin-serve-loop (srv count ledger)
        (if (le count 0) (socket_close srv)
            (do
                (let row (cp-serve-arrival (socket_accept srv) ledger))
                (plugin-serve-loop srv (sub count 1) (cons row ledger)))))

    ;; serve `count` connections on `port`, then close the listener. A witness passes the exact number
    ;; it will send (deterministic stop); a live door passes a large count. The recursion advances on
    ;; count -- the bound is named, never silent. The ledger opens empty with the door.
    (defn plugin-serve (port count)
        (plugin-serve-loop (socket_listen port) count (empty)))

    0)
